Package: citrixscan
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, python3
Description: Full-scope external security scanner for Citrix NetScaler ADC/Gateway
 CitrixScan performs comprehensive, non-exploitative security assessments
 of internet-facing Citrix NetScaler appliances. It identifies firmware
 versions using 10 detection vectors (including GZIP timestamp extraction),
 maps them against 25 known CVEs (2019-2026), detects indicators of
 compromise from known webshell campaigns, audits for security
 misconfigurations, and checks TLS/cipher configurations.
 .
 Features:
  - 228-entry GZIP timestamp fingerprint database
  - 25 CVEs with version-to-fix mapping and config prerequisite checks
  - IoC detection for CVE-2023-3519 webshell campaigns (CISA AA23-201A)
  - Misconfiguration audit with login-page false positive filtering
  - TLS/cipher audit and security header checks
  - JSON, CSV, and Markdown report export
 .
 Single file, zero external dependencies, production-safe.
